						<div id="siteNotice"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>
						<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">chroot</span></h1>
						<div id="bodyContent">
								<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-navigation">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>A <b>chroot</b> on <a href="Unix.html" title="Unix">Unix</a> <a href="Operating_system.html" title="Operating system">operating systems</a> is an operation that changes the apparent <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Root_directory" title="Root directory">root directory</a> for the current running process and its <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Child_process" title="Child process">children</a>. A program that is run in such a modified environment cannot name (and therefore normally not access) files outside the designated directory tree. The term "chroot" may refer to the <tt>chroot(2)</tt> <a href="System_call.html" title="System call">system call</a> or the <tt>chroot(8)</tt> wrapper program. The modified environment is called a "chroot <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jail_(computer_security)" title="Jail (computer security)" class="mw-redirect">jail</a>".</p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
<div id="toctitle">
<h2>Contents</h2>
</div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#History"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">History</span></a></li>
